In memory of my good friend and former personal trainer, Brandon Smith who passed away unexpectedly two years ago on March 22, 2021 at only 30 years of age.

I took this photo of him, half above/below water when we went out paddleboarding on the intracoastal in Jupiter six months before he passed away.  Brandon was a great guy and was like a younger brother to me. 

After I lost my job of 16 years and was able to obtain an even better one just weeks later he sent me the following text (which was one of the last texts he ever sent me):

“Yes!!! Soo proud of you that is awesome! I really look up to you and hope I can be half the man that you are. I usually don’t drink but I would love to take you out for a celebration, maybe at u-tiki or something after a paddleboard session.”

- Miss you buddy, gone way too soon.  Will see you again sometime and we will grab that drink we never had a chance to grab.
